The paper discusses a technique for improving acceptance testing in distributed software projects, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of integrated feedback systems also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and potentially cybersecurity (cs.CY) if security issues are identified during testing. The paper also discusses the communication and collaboration challenges in distributed teams, which could fall under distributed computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
